io.appium.java_client.ios

Class IOSDriver<T extends WebElement>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openqa.selenium.remote.RemoteWebDriver
      • io.appium.java_client.AppiumDriver<T>
        • io.appium.java_client.ios.IOSDriver<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the required type of class which implement WebElement. Instances of the defined type will be returned via findElement* and findElements*. Warning (!!!). Allowed types: WebElement RemoteWebElement MobileElement IOSElement
    All Implemented Interfaces:

      • findElement

        public T findElement(org.openqa.selenium.By by)
        Description copied from interface: WebDriver
        Find the first WebElement using the given method. This method is affected by the 'implicit wait' times in force at the time of execution. The findElement(..) invocation will return a matching row, or try again repeatedly until the configured timeout is reached. findElement should not be used to look for non-present elements, use WebDriver.findElements(By) and assert zero length response instead.
        Specified by:
        findElement in interface MobileDriver<T extends WebElement>
